# Project context (`specs/PROJECT.md`)

**Canonical:** `<repo>/specs/PROJECT.md` holds **#** title, **Intent**, **Technologies**, the spec index, and **AI routing** (see `013-specs-project-entry.mdc`). Workflows and domain matrices stay global (`010-orchestrator.mdc`, `011-orchestrator-reference.mdc`).

## `.cursorrules` — optional

A repo **does not need** `.cursorrules` for the agent stack to work. Use it only if you want **extra** project-injected text in Cursor, or a legacy **Canonical Domains** / **Workflow Auto-Selection** override table. Domain **Technologies** / **Intent** are read from `specs/PROJECT.md` first; if missing, from `.cursorrules`.

## Where everything else lives

| Need | Go to |
|------|--------|
| Workflow for feature / bug / explore / release / security | Global map in `011-orchestrator-reference.mdc` (always applied). |
| Domain (`dart-flutter`, `devops`, …) | **Technologies** in `specs/PROJECT.md` (or `.cursorrules` fallback) + `011-orchestrator-reference.mdc` + open files. |
| Feature rules, BDD, ADRs | `specs/PROJECT.md` → linked specs (agents read on demand). |
| Cross-cutting security / errors / CI | `specs/cross-cutting/*.md` via `PROJECT.md`. |
| MCP servers for this repo | `.cursor/mcp.json` if present. |
| Org-wide skills / AGENTS index | **`$AGENT_KIT/cursor/AGENTS.md`** in **ai-resources** (e.g. ClickUp feature tracking). |
